{
  "texts": [
    "Multi-disciplinary methods spanning computational analytics, focused audits, ethnographic observations and surveys can construct nuanced evaluations across involved stakeholders.",
    "Quantitative researchContent Analysis Studies Longitudinal content analysis enables evaluating utilization and efficacy of notice-and-takedown procedures (Code: NTD) under Article 14 by tracking volumes and categories of disinformation removed over time.",
    "Segmenting takedowns by dimensions like platform, content type, source, and response rates provides granular impact metrics aligned with transparency objectives around illegal content reporting workflows [130].",
    "Advanced text classification techniques can categorize removed content by type, topic, sentiment to provide granular volumetric impact metrics [44].",
    "To audit improvements in advertising transparency under Articles 24 and 30 (Code: AT), content analytics can categorize disclosed ads in mandated repositories by targets, sponsors, geographic origin, topics, and media types."
  ]
}